## M22.1(1/8): resource-producing temporary borrowed with `?` is rejected.
##
## Per GPT-5.5 entry 39: borrowing a fresh `*Cell(...)` via `?`
## yields a borrow over an Rc that has no owner — the strong
## handle gets dropped on the floor as soon as the borrow expires.
## Same leak class as `(*Foo(...)).field`.
##
## V1 policy: bind the *Cell to a name first; the M20e auto-drop
## guard installs at the binding site and the borrow stays valid
## for the binding's scope.

sub main()
  c = ?(*Cell(value: 0))    # error: anonymous *Cell temporary leaks
  print(c.get())
